long_description: thrive advanced care is owned by a board-certified behavior analyst (bcba) provider of aba therapy. we take pride in offering exceptional care to children, ages 2-18, and their family members who are affected by autism spectrum disorder (asd), as well as other behavioral and/or emotional challenges. we understand that these issues, if not addressed, can impede a child from reaching his/her full potential. therefore, our professional behavioral analysts and aba therapy specialists will work hand-in-hand with families, caregivers, teachers and other experts to modify behaviors and help your child begin to thrive. we also understand that positive change takes time and commitment. therefore, we will always go the extra mile to ensure that your child receives our best efforts on their journey toward independence and better behavior.
